@sjfink Can you elaborate what you meant with "it may be better to define a language-neutral attribute on actions".

The way I understand it is: We would have a CLI parameter which determines the entry point for the script like we do in Java but in a standardized way for all languages?

Additionally, several languages could make use of their own ecosystem specificities (like `module.exports` in Node) to lift hard-coded `main` requirement.
